  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n#930 - part 2 - moving the data classes from beacon_chain repo to Py-EVM.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\nIn [beacon_chain repo](https://github.com/ethereum/beacon_chain/tree/master/beacon_chain/state), there some classes:\r\n- active_state.py\r\n- attestation_record.py\r\n- block.py\r\n- crosslink_record.py\r\n- crystallized_state.py\r\n- shard_and_committee.py\r\n- validator_record.py\r\n\r\nIn the Eth2.0 call yesterday, [Alexey pointed out some problems with SimpleSerialize](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-pm/issues/8#issuecomment-424849447). At this point, I suggest we use RLP for now before it's standardized. @djrtwo any thoughts?\r\n\r\nAction:\r\n- Move these classes to `eth/beacon/types/`\r\n- Move tests to `tests/core/beacon/types/`\r\n\r\nNote: there are some handy cache data in `ActiveState`, I think we can remove it and add some other Py-EVM style cache mechanism later.",
